The paper proposes a novel neural topic model using Wasserstein autoencoders, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning for generative modeling. The paper focuses on natural language processing tasks, specifically topic modeling. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the evaluation of topic quality, which suggests a possible fit for cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper uses real datasets and discusses the use of randomness in the encoder output, which could potentially fit into cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well.
